Two men were shot — one fatally — in broad daylight Sunday in Brooklyn, police said. Cops responded to reports of the 1:36 p.m. shooting at Fulton Street and Van Siclen Avenue in Cypress Hills to find a 38-year-old man dead, according to an NYPD spokesperson. The deceased was struck in the armpit, while a 62-year-old man was hit in the left hand, the spokesperson said. The suspect fled west on Fulton Street.